               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321129-203-person1805">
                  GEORGE 
                  ROWLAND
               <interp inst="t18321129-203-person1805" type="surname" value="ROWLAND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-203-person1805" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-203-person1805" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            .I am in the service of Walter Pitman, a <rs id="t18321129-203-viclabel1143" type="occupation">shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321129-203-victim1804 t18321129-203-viclabel1143"></join>. About two o'clock in the afternoon of the 9th of November, I saw the prisoner and another about the shop - I saw the prisoner take three pairs of shoes off the nail at the door, and hand them to his companion, who made off with them - I followed; his companion escaped, but I took the prisoner, without losing sight of him; he dropped a ticket, which had been attached to the shoes - I am positive of him.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321129-203-person1806">
                  THOMAS 
                  BOLTWOOD
               <interp inst="t18321129-203-person1806" type="surname" value="BOLTWOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-203-person1806" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-203-person1806" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I received him in charge.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was in Chiswell-street - two women called out that a man had run away with the shoes; I saw a man running from the shop with them, but lost sight of him; I turned back, and met the prosecutor - the Policeman actually saw the thief run by him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321129-203-person1807">
                  GEORGE 
                  ROWLAND
               <interp inst="t18321129-203-person1807" type="surname" value="ROWLAND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-203-person1807" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-203-person1807" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . He turned round as if to strike me, and the ticket fell from his coat.</p>
